00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:40,000
 loving the family of believers,

228
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,000
 fearing God,

229
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:45,000
 and honoring the Emperor.

230
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:48,000
 And so remember the premise, we do not belong in this world,

231
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:52,000
 but by the way that we live in a world that we do not belong to,

232
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:55,000
 others would be drawn to the king of the world that we belong to,

233
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:57,000
 and they would want to belong to that world.

234
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,000
 You guys get it?

235
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,000
 An illustration.

236
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:07,000
 Jackie Robinson was one of the first African Americans in Major League Baseball.

237
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:11,000
 Branch Rickey, manager of the Dodgers, recruited him,

238
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:14,000
 not because, maybe you've seen the movie 42,

239
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:17,000
 it was a great movie,

240
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:20,000
 one of the things that it left out, I read an article this week in USA Today,

241
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:23,000
 one of the things that the movie 42 left out

242
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:25,000
 was actually all about Jackie Robinson's faith.

243
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:28,000
 He had an incredible faith in Christ.

244
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:32,000
 And the reason Branch Rickey recruited him

245
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:35,000
 was not solely because of his athletic ability.

246
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:40,000
 There were other African Americans who could really play the game of baseball.

247
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:43,000
 But the article said that Branch Rickey recruited him

248
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:46,000
 because of his faith and honorable character.

249
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:51,000
 Now why? Why would Branch Rickey hold dearly to faith and honorable character?

250
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,000
 Here's why.

251
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:55,000
 Because he knew that he was going to move Jackie Robinson

252
00:15:55,000 --> 00:16:00,000
 into an incredibly corrupt and turmoil organization

253
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,000
 where people were going to persecute him,

254
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:06,000
 say awful things about him, bring death threats to him,

255
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:09,000
 bring death threats to his loved ones,

256
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:12,000
 and the only way that this African American

257
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:16,000
 was going to be able to persevere through this

258
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:20,000
 was if he had a faith in something bigger than himself.

259
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:24,000
 Was if he could trust or be under an authority

260
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:27,000
 greater than the authority of this world.

261
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:30,000
 And as we know, so Jackie Robinson moves to the team,

262
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:33,000
 the team actually creates a petition to get him off the team,

263
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:37,000
 his own teammates, out of their own ignorance and closed-mindedness,

264
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:39,000
 they want him off the team.

265
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:41,000
 And he wins them over how? By his conduct,

266
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,000
 by the way he responded to people,

267
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:46,000
 and by the way he played the game with excellence.

268
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:49,000
 And in the same way, this is why you work,

269
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,000
 this is how you are a citizen,

270
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:53,000
 this is how you are a contributor in your church,

271
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:57,000
 that others would see your conduct and glorify your Father in Heaven.

272
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:01,000
 Man, I want to know what team they play for.

273
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:04,000
 I want to play for their manager.

274
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:07,000
 I don't like them, I don't agree with them,

275
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:10,000
 but they've got my attention.

276
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:12,000
 Because of the way that they live,

277
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:14,000
 because of how they do good,

278
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:18,000
 and because of how they do things with excellence.

279
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:22,000
 And so we live as free people,

280
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:24,000
 not free from authority,

281
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:27,000
 but freed to honor authority

282
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:30,000
 because of what Christ has done for us,

283
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,000
 free from rebelling against authority

284
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,000
 in a way that doesn't honor God.

285
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,000
 Everyone is rebellious in nature,

286
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,000
 we see that in Weston at one and a half years old,

287
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:41,000
 that he didn't have to learn to be a rebel, right?

288
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:43,000
 It comes natural to him,

289
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:46,000
 and it comes natural to you,

290
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:48,000
 but the way that you're different than the world

291
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:51,000
 is you are free not to rebel.

292
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:58,000
 And so, for the purpose of winning others to ultimate authority,

293
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,000
 and so what authorities are over us?

294
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:03,000
 My second point this evening, or second question,

295
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,000
 what authorities are over us?

296
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:07,000
 Let's understand that it says every human authority,

297
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:11,000
 in fact in 1 Peter 5, verse 5, same book, different chapter,

298
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:14,000
 it says that we're actually to submit to those who are older than us,

299
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:16,000
 not even talking about elders of a church,

300
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,000
 but just simply older people,

301
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:21,000
 that there's this kind of hierarchy even in society.

302
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:23,000
 And so it says to every human authority,

303
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:27,000
 but I think of the three that this Scripture covers,

304
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:29,000
 and three very relevant to young adults,

305
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,000
 is the first one is the government.

306
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,000
 We're to submit to the government.

307
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,000
 What does that look like?

308
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,000
 We obey the laws, okay?

309
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,000
 The other day I got pulled over for speeding, okay?

310
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,000
 Long story, it's not really a long story,

311
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:42,000
 I was speeding, I got pulled over, that's the story.

312
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:45,000
 You know what the first thing that went through my mind was?

313
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,000
 This is the first, I'm sure I'm alone on this,

314
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,000
 I'm sure you guys don't think this way,

315
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:51,000
 but because I'm so rebellious,

316
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:53,000
 the first thing that goes through my mind is,

317
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:56,000
 "How do I get out of this ticket?"

318
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:58,000
 Okay?

319
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,000
 In spite of my efforts, I got the ticket,

320
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:02,000
 and do you know what the second thing on my mind was?

321
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:05,000
 After I received the piece of paper that was a ticket?

322
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:08,000
 "How do I get out of paying this ticket?"

323
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,000
 Right?

324
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,000
 Why?

325
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,000
 Because I'm rebellious.

326
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:15,000
 Because I do not like an authority over me.

327
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,000
 Let me say it like this,

328
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:19,000
 I do not like to submit to authority.

329
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:22,000
 I don't even want the consequences from my action.

330
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:25,000
 I want to be free from the consequences for my action.

331
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:30,000
 I want to feel like I am above authority.

332
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:33,000
 I do not want to submit.

333
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:36,000
 But this scripture has incredible implications for us.

334
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:38,000
 It's not only that we obey the laws,

335
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:40,000
 but that we would honor, it says, the president,

336
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:43,000
 it says the emperor, but in our implications, the president.

337
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:46,000
 That we do not slander our president.

338
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,000
 Wow.

339
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:51,000
 That you can express your opinion,

340
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:55,000
 but make sure your conduct is louder than your speech.

341
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,000
 What this means is that maybe you have an opinion

342
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:01,000
 about marriage or abortion or about health care

343
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:03,000
 or about POW exchanges.

344
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:05,000
 Maybe you have opinions about these things,

345
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:08,000
 but you make sure your conduct is louder

346
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:11,000
 than the way that you speak about those in authority over you

347
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,000
 so that others would see your conduct and say,

348
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:17,000
 "Man, I want to listen to what they have to say.

349
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:19,000
 "I don't just, the way she lives her life above her approach,

350
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:24,000
 "the way he lives his life, I'm listening.

351
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:29,000
 "And if he tells me abortion's wrong, I'm curious at least.

352
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:33,000
 "I want to understand why."

353
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:38,000
 And so, maybe right now you're thinking,

354
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:41,000
 "Well, what if he's, what if the authority over me,

355
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:44,000
 "what if the government that is placed over me at some point,

356
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:47,000
 "what if they're wicked, what if they're corrupt?"

357
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:52,000
 Cool. Let's talk about Nero for a second, okay?

358
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,000
 Nero was not just a government raising your taxes

359
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:58,000
 or passing bad health care.

360
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:02,000
 Nero was a cross-dresser who was burning Christians alive.

361
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:05,000
 He killed his mother and his first wife.

362
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:09,000
 He married a boy child, had him castrated,

363
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:16,000
 and had him dress up like a woman and pretend to be his wife.

364
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:24,000
 And God, through Peter, is saying, "Honor that man."

365
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:27,000
 Okay, so whatever government you have over you

366
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:31,000
 at any time in the future, you go back and you look at Nero,

367
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:36,000
 this guy seems to have, and I want to say something slanderous about him,

368
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:39,000
 but I was encouraged not to, so I wouldn't even break the rule here.

369
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:42,000
 It's interesting that the Scripture never does.

370
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:45,000
 History tells us some crazy things about him,

371
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:47,000
 but the Scripture never slanders him.

372
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:50,000
 In fact, the Scripture tells us to honor him.

373
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:54,000
 By the way, the very man who penned this letter,

374
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:57,000
 Nero crucified him upside down.

375
00:21:57,000 --> 00:22:06,000
 The very man asking you to honor him was crucified upside down.

376
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:09,000
 Here's what this means.

377
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:14,000
 Whether you wear your seatbelt or stay under the speed limit

378
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:20,000
 or slander the president has implications to God.

379
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:24,000
 In fact, his glory is at stake.

380
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:27,000
 Why? God cares.

381
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:32,000
 That is what this Scripture is pointing out to us.

382
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:35,000
 And so I would just encourage you to pray for President Obama

383
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:38,000
 more than you slander him.

384
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:43,000
 Consider what would happen if all of your prayers for him were answered

385
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:46,000
 and live in such a way that others would be drawn to your opinion

386
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:49,000
 because of how you live and conduct,

387
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:52,000
 how you live and act around these issues.

388
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:55,000
 Fear God and honor the president, the Scripture says.

389
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:58,000
 The second thing that we submit to from the Scripture

390
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:01,000
 is we submit to our employer, the one who is over us.

391
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:03,000
 It says this in verse 18,

392
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:06,000
 "Slaves, in reverent fear of God, submit yourselves to your masters."

393
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:09,000
 Now, slaves and masters in this culture, it's not a racial slavery.

394
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,000
 That's important to know.

395
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:14,000
 All we know in this world is a racial slavery,

396
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:19,000
 or at least in our culture is a racial slavery in recent history.

397
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:21,000
 But here it's not a racial slavery.

398
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:24,000
 It's actually an agreement that, hey, you would work here

399
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:26,000
 and I would give you provision for life.

400
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:28,000
 That's the slave and master relationship.

401
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:31,000
 It's the closest thing that we have to an employee-employer relationship.

402
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:34,000
 And so read here, "Employees, in reverent fear of God,

403
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:36,000
 "submit yourself to your employers,

404
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:39,000
 "not only to those who are good and considerate,

405
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:41,000
 "but also to those who are harsh."

406
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:45,000
 The Scripture says that bad employers are a reality

407
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:49,000
 and that we're to submit ourselves to those who are even harsh.

408
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:51,000
 It says, "In reverent fear of God."

409
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:53,000
 That's, again, important.

410
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:57,000
 Not because you fear man, not because you fear consequences,

411
00:23:57,000 --> 00:24:01,000
 but only because you fear God Almighty.

412
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:04,000
 And, of course, you can sin in how you submit

413
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:06,000
 if your perspective is off.

414
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:10,000
 And so this slave-master relationship, though it was not a racial slavery,

415
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:13,000
 it was also not always a pleasant relationship.

416
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:15,000
 And so anybody here have a bad boss?

417
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:18,000
 Don't raise your hand because they may be behind you.

418
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:20,000
 And you don't know it.

419
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:24,000
 And so certainly some folks here have had or currently have

420
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:27,000
 or will have a bad supervisor, a bad boss.

421
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:31,000
 Let me tell you that the Scripture's going to paint a picture of a bad supervisor.

422
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:34,000
 "For it is commendable," God commends you,

423
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:38,000
 "if someone bears up under the pain," and it means pain there,

424
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:42,000
 "of unjust suffering because they are conscious of God.

425
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:45,000
 "But how is it to your credit if you receive a beating,"

426
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:49,000
 and it means beating, "for doing wrong and endure it?

427
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:52,000
 "But if you suffer for doing good and you endure it,

428
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:55,000
 "this is commendable before God."

429
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:58,000
 And so I don't know what your boss has done,

430
00:24:58,000 --> 00:25:01,000
 but my hunch is he hasn't beaten you.

431
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,000
 Right?

432
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:05,000
 And so the Scripture is painting a picture

433
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:07,000
 that the reason that you work,

434
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:10,000
 that that employer-employee relationship

435
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:15,000
 goes far beyond if you like your job.

436
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:18,000
 It goes far beyond if you like what you're doing.

437
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:21,000
 It goes far beyond if you're passionate about it.

438
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:24,000
 And it says the reason that you are there

439
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:26,000
 is because of some other relationship,

440
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:30,000
 so that others would see you being the most excellent person there

441
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:32,000
 and honoring your God,

442
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:35,000
 and in fact the persecution that you endure there,

443
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:37,000
 it says it is commendable to God.

444
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:40,000
 And this is why we talk about work so much,

445
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:42,000
 because what we do in our generation,

446
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:44,000
 and I've done it too, I'm completely guilty of this,

447
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:47,000
 is I jump into a job until it's difficult,

448
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:48,000
 and then I jump out.

449
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:50,000
 Like, "It's not God's will that I be there."

450
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:53,000
 And then I jump into another job until it's difficult,

451
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:56,000
 and then I'm like, "Well, it's not God's will that I be there either."

452
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:58,000
 And so I jump into another job,

453
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:00,000
 and so we know statistically our generation

454
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:04,000
 is only at an employer for about two years,

455
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:10,000
 which is a historical low by years,

456
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:13,000
 because we're looking for contentment at work

457
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:17,000
 when the Scriptures tell us that we're not entitled to it.

458
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:19,000
 In fact, it says work is hard and work is toilsome,

459
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:22,000
 as we covered a few weeks ago.

460
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:24,000
 But it says that if you suffer for doing good,

461
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:27,000
 it is commendable before God.

462
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:29,000
 Colossians 3, verse 22, says it like this.

463
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:31,000
 Slaves, read employees,

464
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:35,000
 obey your earthly employers in everything and do it,

465
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:38,000
 not only when their eye is on you to curry their favor,

466
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:40,000
 which is what we often do, like, "Hey, if he's looking,

467
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:42,000
 "like, I'm going to do everything I'm supposed to do."

468
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:47,000
 But with sincerity of heart and reverence for the Lord.

469
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:49,000
 Whatever you do, work at it with all your heart

470
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:52,000
 as working for the Lord, not for human masters.

471
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:54,000
 Since you know that you will receive an inheritance

472
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:56,000
 from the Lord as a reward,

473
00:26:56,000 --> 00:27:01,000
 it is the Lord Christ you are serving.

474
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:06,000
 Here's my quick summary of the second part of that passage.

475
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:09,000
 God distributes the promotions.

476
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:13,000
 God's in charge of the promotions.

477
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:19,000
 God chooses who gets promoted and who doesn't.

478
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:22,000
 The rewards are up to God.

479
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:23,000
 Do you believe that?

