 It was the reason God used it to change my life,

988
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:29,000
 or it's a silly story, I'll say.

989
00:48:29,000 --> 00:48:31,000
 It's actually a children's story.

990
00:48:31,000 --> 00:48:35,000
 It comes from this book I later found out.

991
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:38,000
 The book I read to my little girls now,

992
00:48:38,000 --> 00:48:40,000
 Adventures of Thunder Hoof.

993
00:48:40,000 --> 00:48:42,000
 (congregation laughing)

994
00:48:42,000 --> 00:48:45,000
 Here's the story.

995
00:48:45,000 --> 00:48:47,000
 There was a wild stallion that just wanted to be free.

996
00:48:47,000 --> 00:48:49,000
 Man, I can relate to that.

997
00:48:49,000 --> 00:48:51,000
 I'm listening.

998
00:48:51,000 --> 00:48:53,000
 He wanted to be free, man.

999
00:48:53,000 --> 00:48:55,000
 He rode a horse, and he roamed the mountainside

1000
00:48:55,000 --> 00:48:57,000
 in search of freedom.

1001
00:48:57,000 --> 00:48:59,000
 And in his freedom, he had to hunt for food

1002
00:48:59,000 --> 00:49:02,000
 and hunt for water and find protection

1003
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:04,000
 from the elements, from the storms and the rains

1004
00:49:04,000 --> 00:49:06,000
 that would come.

1005
00:49:06,000 --> 00:49:08,000
 And people would try to capture this horse,

1006
00:49:08,000 --> 00:49:10,000
 but they would fail.

1007
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:14,000
 And one day, this farmer, this cowboy,

1008
00:49:14,000 --> 00:49:17,000
 successfully captured this horse, this wild stallion,

1009
00:49:17,000 --> 00:49:21,000
 and he took him home, and he loved him,

1010
00:49:21,000 --> 00:49:24,000
 and he cared for him, and he provided for him.

1011
00:49:24,000 --> 00:49:26,000
 And through that love, care, and provision,

1012
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:30,000
 eventually he was able to break this horse.

1013
00:49:30,000 --> 00:49:33,000
 And in breaking this horse, he was able to mount this horse

1014
00:49:33,000 --> 00:49:35,000
 and ride this horse.

1015
00:49:35,000 --> 00:49:37,000
 And in riding this horse, he would lead him to food,

1016
00:49:37,000 --> 00:49:39,000
 and he would lead him to water,

1017
00:49:39,000 --> 00:49:44,000
 and he would lead him to protection from the elements.

1018
00:49:44,000 --> 00:49:47,000
 And it was this line that changed my life.

1019
00:49:47,000 --> 00:49:52,000
 It wasn't until he was fully submissive to his master

1020
00:49:52,000 --> 00:49:55,000
 that he truly experienced freedom.

1021
00:49:55,000 --> 00:49:59,000
 And I realized that I had been wearing myself out

1022
00:49:59,000 --> 00:50:03,000
 in pursuit of freedom, all while taking this for granted,

1023
00:50:03,000 --> 00:50:06,000
 telling you that I believed this, but doing nothing

1024
00:50:06,000 --> 00:50:09,000
 that would tell you that I actually believed this.

1025
00:50:09,000 --> 00:50:11,000
 Telling you that I was a part of the church,

1026
00:50:11,000 --> 00:50:14,000
 but not belonging anywhere, podcasting this guy,

1027
00:50:14,000 --> 00:50:19,000
 podcasting that guy, whatever, but not belonging anywhere.

1028
00:50:19,000 --> 00:50:25,000
 Telling you that I loved God, but doing whatever I wanted.

1029
00:50:25,000 --> 00:50:27,000
 And I sat there, and I said this prayer.

1030
00:50:27,000 --> 00:50:32,000
 I said, "Lord, if you're God, if you created everything,

1031
00:50:32,000 --> 00:50:36,000
 "then you know how to do life so much better than I do.

1032
00:50:36,000 --> 00:50:38,000
 "I've heard you sent your son to die for my sins.

1033
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:40,000
 "This is good, 'cause I need someone to pay for my sins.

1034
00:50:40,000 --> 00:50:43,000
 "There's a lot of them.

1035
00:50:43,000 --> 00:50:45,000
 "Lord, would you drive?

1036
00:50:45,000 --> 00:50:47,000
 "Lord, would you show me where to go?

1037
00:50:47,000 --> 00:50:50,000
 "Lord, I submit my life to your care now,

1038
00:50:50,000 --> 00:50:53,000
 "through the death and the resurrection of your son Jesus,

1039
00:50:53,000 --> 00:50:56,000
 "believing that he died for my sins.

1040
00:50:56,000 --> 00:50:58,000
 "Father, would you give me new life?"

1041
00:50:58,000 --> 00:51:00,000
 And he did.

1042
00:51:00,000 --> 00:51:05,000
 And what he killed in that moment was my rebellious spirit.

1043
00:51:05,000 --> 00:51:07,000
 Every now and then it flares up,

1044
00:51:07,000 --> 00:51:10,000
 but he's gracious to remind me who he is

1045
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:14,000
 in charge, and that he works through bosses,

1046
00:51:14,000 --> 00:51:16,000
 and that he works through governments,

1047
00:51:16,000 --> 00:51:19,000
 and that he works through churches to bring about his will.

1048
00:51:19,000 --> 00:51:23,000
 And my job is to do as they've asked,

1049
00:51:23,000 --> 00:51:26,000
 as long as it does not dishonor him.

1050
00:51:26,000 --> 00:51:28,000
 I pray that you would do the same.

1051
00:51:28,000 --> 00:51:30,000
 Let me do that now.

1052
00:51:37,000 --> 00:51:38,000
 Father, help us.

1053
00:51:38,000 --> 00:51:41,000
 There is something inside of us

1054
00:51:41,000 --> 00:51:46,000
 that wants to run when we hear the word stop,

1055
00:51:46,000 --> 00:51:51,000
 that wants to stop when we hear the word run,

1056
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:54,000
 that wants to flee when we hear the word submit,

1057
00:51:54,000 --> 00:51:56,000
 that wants to fight.

1058
00:51:56,000 --> 00:51:58,000
 And Lord, we realize now,

1059
00:51:58,000 --> 00:52:00,000
 through the reading of your scriptures

1060
00:52:00,000 --> 00:52:03,000
 and the understanding of the things that you have told us to,

1061
00:52:03,000 --> 00:52:04,000
 the eternal truths,

1062
00:52:04,000 --> 00:52:08,000
 that victory actually comes through surrender,

1063
00:52:08,000 --> 00:52:13,000
 that freedom actually comes through submission.

1064
00:52:13,000 --> 00:52:16,000
 So Lord, would you help us to find freedom

1065
00:52:16,000 --> 00:52:18,000
 through submission,

1066
00:52:18,000 --> 00:52:20,000
 first and foremost to you,

1067
00:52:20,000 --> 00:52:23,000
 and then to every human authority that you have put in place,

1068
00:52:23,000 --> 00:52:26,000
 that you are actually the authority over.

1069
00:52:26,000 --> 00:52:29,000
 Lord, we love you, and we trust you.

1070
00:52:29,000 --> 00:52:31,000
 Help us be free.

1071
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:33,000
 Amen.

1072
00:52:34,000 --> 00:52:37,000
 It's strange, you know, the Christian faith,

1073
00:52:37,000 --> 00:52:40,000
 the God who created the whole world,

1074
00:52:40,000 --> 00:52:44,000
 that there's these strange, like, contradictions,

1075
00:52:44,000 --> 00:52:49,000
 these weird paradoxes that victory,

1076
00:52:49,000 --> 00:52:52,000
 like winning victory,

1077
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:55,000
 would come through surrender.

1078
00:52:55,000 --> 00:52:57,000
 That it's like when you come to this place where you're like,

1079
00:52:57,000 --> 00:53:00,000
 "I can't. I'm not good enough.

1080
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:03,000
 I'm not fast enough or strong enough or smart enough."

1081
00:53:03,000 --> 00:53:06,000
 But God, I'm your servant,

1082
00:53:06,000 --> 00:53:09,000
 that you find victory then.

1083
00:53:09,000 --> 00:53:13,000
 And that freedom, like we have this desire in us

1084
00:53:13,000 --> 00:53:15,000
 to be free, but we look for that,

1085
00:53:15,000 --> 00:53:17,000
 we look to fulfill that desire in all the wrong things

1086
00:53:17,000 --> 00:53:19,000
 through our own accomplishments.

1087
00:53:19,000 --> 00:53:22,000
 We find self-worth through the things that we do,

1088
00:53:22,000 --> 00:53:25,000
 but that real freedom actually comes

1089
00:53:25,000 --> 00:53:30,000
 through tapping out, through surrender.

1090
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:33,000
 Through surrender, like, "I can't.

1091
00:53:33,000 --> 00:53:36,000
 God, I need your help.

1092
00:53:36,000 --> 00:53:38,000
 Lord, I'm listening. You speak.

1093
00:53:38,000 --> 00:53:41,000
 Lord, I'll go. You send.

1094
00:53:41,000 --> 00:53:43,000
 Father, help me."

1095
00:53:43,000 --> 00:53:49,000
 [silence]

